   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>H. C. To the Gentleman Reader.</head>
   <l>IF thou desire to knowe the reason why,</l>
   <l>Thou doo'st in Sheild the Armes of honour bear,</l>
   <l>This Booke will say that they by nature were</l>
   <l>The <hi>HIEROGLYPHICKS</hi> of Nobility.</l>
   <l>It shewes beside, how <hi>Art</hi> doth beautifie</l>
   <l>What <hi>Nature</hi> doth inspire, and how each-where</l>
   <l>All <hi>Arts</hi> conion'd in this <hi>Art</hi> do appeare,</l>
   <l>By structure of a choyce Phylosophie.</l>
   <l>
      <hi>GEOMETRIE</hi> giues Lines in ordred Place,</l>
   <l>Numbers <hi>ARITHMETICK,</hi> and thou may'st see</l>
   <l>How all in <hi>OPTICK</hi> Colours honour thee.</l>
   <l>But since <hi>that Virtue</hi> which adorn'd the race</l>
   <l>From whence thou did'st descend was ground of al,</l>
   <l>Haue care to follow it, or all will fall.</l>
